meanings.definition: To launch or introduce (something) before the official launch date or time.
meanings.sent1: The company prelaunched their new product to a select group of customers.
meanings.sent2: The team decided to prelaunch the website to test its functionality.
meanings.sent3: The cat prelaunched itself onto the unsuspecting dog, causing chaos in the living room.
meanings.sent4: The idea prelaunched into the market, capturing the attention of early adopters.
meanings.sent5: The rocket prelaunched into the sky, leaving a trail of excitement behind.

meanings.definition: Having been launched or introduced before the official launch date or time.
meanings.sent1: The prelaunched product received positive feedback from early users.
meanings.sent2: The prelaunched app had a head start in the competitive market.
meanings.sent3: The prelaunched balloon floated gracefully above the crowd, drawing everyone's attention.
meanings.sent4: Her prelaunched career took off faster than expected, surprising many in the industry.
meanings.sent5: The prelaunched event created a buzz among attendees, making it a highly anticipated affair.
